Your 100% right @h3llrais3r ! :).   My comment must have gotten misinterpreted (sometimes i don't explain myself properly).  I thought you guys were discussing separating scoring into it's own class and processing.  I'm kind of just saying: that's a lot of extra work for very little gain.  I understand the need to not score at times (in the new design @Diaoul is proposing) to display all matches.  But I'm just trying to say: don't do this... do the scoring always and every time right away.  But then choose to filter the results on demand (from a functional purpose).

@Diaoul: I honestly can't think of a use case where anyone would ever want to write a custom scoring feature especially since some sites return more or less information (addicted vs podnapisi for example). Subliminal is solid as it is; it's best feature is allowing people to write their own subliminal scraper for their own favorite site (and new ones that pop up).  That is just my two cents though :).

