So I think I figured out that the Flask process doesn't know the client is disconnected. Only after it tries to send something again it will realize that there is no longer a client on the other side and fails silently. 

The following code catches this:
```python
@stream_with_context
def generator():
    try:
        for message in self.messages(channel=channel):
            yield str(message)
    except:
        current_app.logger.debug('client disconnected')
````

